text: Quebrada de Piedra is a corregimiento in Tolé District, Chiriquí Province, Panama. It has a land area of and had a population of 1,127 as of 2010, giving it a population density of . Its population as of 1990 was 1,197; its population as of 2000 was 1,209. ==References== Category:Corregimientos of Chiriquí Province
